                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17386</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-09T16:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Villa thought to have gone back to his camp at point described in my March 7, 8
                    p.m. Villa positively with attacking party in Columbus.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
